---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'April 2026';
---
<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — Dr. Gore"
  description="Privacy policy for drgore.com — how we collect, use, and protect your personal information."
  canonical="https://drgore.com/privacy"
  noIndex={true}
>
  <section class="py-20">
    <div class="container max-w-3xl">
      <h1 class="font-display text-4xl font-bold text-foreground mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mb-10">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
      <div class="space-y-8 text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">

        <p>
          Dr. David Karol Gore, Ph.D., P.C. ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting
          your privacy. This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, and safeguard your
          personal information when you visit drgore.com or submit an inquiry through our
          contact form.
        </p>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-3">1. Information We Collect</h2>
          <p class="mb-3">
            <strong class="text-foreground">Contact form submissions:</strong> When you reach out via our website,
            we collect your name, email address, phone number (optional), and the message you provide.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong class="text-foreground">Automatically collected data:</strong> Like most websites, our hosting
            provider (Vercel) automatically collects standard server log data, including your IP address,
            browser type, referring URL, and pages visited. This data is used for security and
            operational monitoring only.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-3">2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
          <p>
            Information submitted through our contact form is used solely to respond to your inquiry
            and, if appropriate, to schedule a consultation. We do not use your information for
            marketing purposes, and we do not sell, rent, or share your personal information with
            any third party except as required to deliver our services (see Section 4) or as
            required by law.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-3">3. Confidentiality and HIPAA</h2>
          <p class="mb-3">
            All communication and information exchanged during therapy sessions is protected by
            professional confidentiality obligations and, where applicable, the Health Insurance
            Portability and Accountability Act (HIPAA). Protected Health Information (PHI) is
            handled strictly in accordance with our Notice of Privacy Practices.
          </p>
          <p>
            Please note: our website contact form is <strong class="text-foreground">not</strong> a secure
            medical communications channel. Do not submit sensitive clinical information through the
            contact form. For clinical matters, please call us directly at (404) 237-4300.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-3">4. Third-Party Services</h2>
          <p class="mb-3">
            We use the following third-party services to operate this website:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 pl-2">
            <li>
              <strong class="text-foreground">Vercel</strong> — website hosting and serverless infrastructure.
              Vercel processes server request logs in accordance with their privacy policy.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="text-foreground">Resend</strong> — transactional email delivery. Contact form
              submissions are transmitted via Resend to deliver your message to our inbox.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">
            Neither service receives PHI. Contact form data transmitted through these services is
            limited to the information you provide (name, email, phone, message).
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-3">5. Cookies</h2>
          <p>
            This website does not use tracking cookies or advertising pixels. We do not use Google
            Analytics or any behavioral tracking technology. Any cookies set are strictly functional
            (e.g., load-balancing cookies set by our hosting provider).
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-3">6. Data Retention</h2>
          <p>
            Contact form inquiries are retained only as long as necessary to respond to your
            request and, if a therapeutic relationship is established, in accordance with applicable
            records retention requirements (typically seven years after termination of services in
            Georgia, or longer if required by law). Server logs are retained per Vercel's standard
            retention policy.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-3">7. Your Rights</h2>
          <p>
            You may request access to, correction of, or deletion of personal information we hold
            about you by contacting us at the address below. Requests relating to PHI are governed
            by our HIPAA Notice of Privacy Practices.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-3">8. Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            Our website is not directed to children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect
            personal information from children under 13 through this website. If you are a parent
            seeking services for a minor, please contact us directly by phone.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-3">9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p>
            We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. The "Last updated" date at the top of
            this page reflects the most recent revision. Continued use of our website after any
            update constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-3">10. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or how your information is handled,
            please contact:
          </p>
          <address class="not-italic mt-3 space-y-1">
            <p class="font-medium text-foreground">Dr. David Karol Gore, Ph.D., P.C.</p>
            <p>6065 Lake Forrest Drive, Suite 250</p>
            <p>Atlanta, GA 30328</p>
            <p><a href="tel:+14042374300" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors" data-gtag-event="phone_click" data-gtag-source="privacy_page">(404) 237-4300</a></p>
            <p><a href="mailto:dave@drgore.com" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors" data-gtag-event="email_click" data-gtag-source="privacy_page">dave@drgore.com</a></p>
          </address>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
